I see you are choosing to ignore robots.txt going by your order file 
posted above.  Please then remove the &#39;heritrix&#39; from your &#39;user-agent&#39; 
identifier and from your &#39;from&#39; address so the software itself doesn&#39;t 
get mislabelled a miscreant, non-honoring of robots.txt, by an overtaxed 
NYT webmaster and so we aren&#39;t contacted if complaints about a robot 
roaming in barred locales.

Look at your &#39;credential-domain&#39; configuration.  It has a &#39;http://&#39; 
prefix.  It shouldn&#39;t have it here.  That looks like it might be the 
problem (smile).  I&#39;ll clean up doc. and help text hereabouts.

This login stuff is awkward to debug -- especially on large sites.  Work 
on specifying as narrow a crawl as possible.  To aid debugging, add 
&#39;org.archive.crawler.fetcher.FetchHTTP.level = FINE&#39; to 
&#39;conf/heritrix.properties&#39; and restart.  It&#39;ll output more detail on 
what the http fetcher is doing.  The logs will  not say if the auth has 
been successful or not -- the breadth of possible success indicators is 
too vast -- but you&#39;ll at least be able to see POST and setup of auth 
submission.

